gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 129, Knicks 120
gameRecap.excerpt: Jalen Williams (career-high 36 points) and Shai-Gilgeous Alexander (36 points, seven rebounds, eight assists) combine for 72 points to lead the Thunder over the Knicks, 129-120.  Chet Holmgren added 22 points, five rebounds and four blocks in the victory, while Julius Randle (25 points, nine rebounds) and Jalen Brunson (24 points, seven assists) combined for 49 points for the Knicks in the losing effort.  The Thunder improve to 20-9 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 17-13.
